      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s even worse than that, actually. Looks like the current code is broken and would allow you to do something like:\n\nsomeEnum.sk_FragCoord;\n\nbecause the symbol lookup for sk_FragCoord would fail and fall back to the parent, which does contain sk_FragCoord (and is a var), so it would actually pass this check.\n\nI think the core issue is that the symboltable for the enum fields is created with a parent (SkSLIRGenerator:1268). Seems like we should fix that first. Then there\u0027s no possibility of this lookup not resulting in a variable since there\u0027s no fallback case, and we can just assert that it\u0027s a VariableReference here.\n\nBrian, do you want me to put together a CL for that, or do you want to tackle it?",
